column2: What is your age? (please only enter a number in years)
column3: How would you self-identify in terms of your Spanish language ability?
column4: Have you ever traveled to a Spanish-speaking country, and, if so, did you communicate in Spanish while in that Spanish-speaking country?
column5: Have you ever traveled to a Spanish-speaking country on an education-focused travel-abroad program?
column6: Did you have any significant exposure to Spanish before the age of 10? (significant could mean: a family member spoke to you; you lived in a Spanish-speaking country; you took a Spanish class; etc.)
column7: Have you ever received formal Spanish language instruction?
column8: If you have you received formal Spanish language instruction, approximately how many years? (Assume each college semester = 1 year; each High School course = 1 year) If not, please enter "0".
column9: If you have you ever received formal Spanish language instruction, have you every been explicitly taught Spanish pronunciation?
column10: How often do you have exposure to Spanish (outside of a classroom setting)?
column11: How often do you speak in Spanish (outside of a classroom setting)?
column12: When was the last time you spoke Spanish (outside of a classroom setting)?
column13: Are you currently trying to learn Spanish?
